{
  "texts": [
    "Many thinkers have argued that attitude consists of affective and cognitive components (Kabra et al., 2023; Montano and Kasprzyk, 2015).",
    "Davis (1985) asserted that perceived usefulness and perceived ease of use have beneficial effects on attitudes toward information technology.",
    "Put another way, people are more inclined to adopt a technology positively when they perceive it as being more beneficial and easier to use.",
    "Numerous information technologies have been predicted and explained by TAM, and the suggested connections have often been confirmed (Larue and Watling, 2021).",
    "Adu-Gyamfi et al. (2022) used TAM to explain drivers' perceptions of the onboard monitoring system."
  ]
}